# Prompt: Update Analytics Configuration to Read Environment Variables from the Project
## Objective
The Cloudflare Pages project has already been configured with all required **Environment Variables**.
Update the analytics implementation so it automatically reads configuration from the project's environment variables instead of using hardcoded values.
The implementation must work in:
* Local development (`.env.local`)
* Cloudflare Pages Preview
* Cloudflare Pages Production
No code changes should be required when deploying between environments.
---
# Existing Environment Variables
The following variables are already configured in the Cloudflare Pages project.
```text
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_ANALYTICS
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLARITY_PROJECT_ID
NEXT_PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_DEBUG
```
Do not hardcode any IDs or keys.
Always read them from `process.env`.
---
# Create Centralized Configuration
Create a single configuration module.
Example location
```text
src/config/analytics.ts
```
This module should expose
* analytics enabled
* GA Measurement ID
* PostHog Key
* PostHog Host
* Clarity Project ID
* Debug Mode
The rest of the application must import configuration only from this module.
Never access `process.env` directly outside this file.
---
# Validation
Validate all configuration values during application startup.
If analytics are disabled
```text
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=false
```
Do not initialize any provider.
If a provider is missing required configuration
Examples
Missing GA Measurement ID
Missing PostHog Key
Missing Clarity Project ID
Skip initializing only that provider.
Do not crash the application.
Display warnings only in development mode.
Example
```text
[Analytics]
Google Analytics disabled
Reason:
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID is missing.
```
---
# Provider Initialization
Update all providers.
Google Analytics
Initialize only when
* analytics enabled
* Measurement ID exists
Microsoft Clarity
Initialize only when
* analytics enabled
* Project ID exists
PostHog
Initialize only when
* analytics enabled
* API Key exists
